The shoggoth is incapable of computationally or semantically relevant phenomenal binding.

Whatever phenomenal binding does occur in the shoggoth, it does not feed back into any computation. And it is hardware-specific. It's what @webmasterdave describes as "psychotic binding". https://t.co/XdbpoYMvvy

@webmasterdave Not to be confused with DMT shoggoths, which emerge out of the resonance between internal representations of other people. A DMT shoggoth does use phenomenal binding.

Note that "failed annealing" is needed for DMT shoggoth emergence. They "coagulate" rather than "click".

@webmasterdave DMT shoggoths that emerge this way are, IMO, what people are talking about when they encounter "egregores" in hyperspace.

It's more like an amalgam of interpersonal representations with semi-coherent goals and vibes. Remarkably, DMT shoggoths are never entirely self-consistent.

